<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader to Attend Brunei Sultan's Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- First Secretary of the Myanmar
State Peace and Development Council (SPDC) lt. Gen. Khin Nyunt
left here Monday for Brunei to attend a ceremony honoring the 52nd
birthday of Brunei Sultan Hassanal Bolkiah, state-run TV Myanmar
reported.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by his wife Daw Khin Win Shwe and deputy foreign
minister U Khin Maung Win, Khin Nyunt is making the trip at the
invitation of the Brunei Sultan.
</P>
<P>
The Brunei Sultan paid a state visit to Myanmar in May in
return for the one made in April by Senior-Gen. Than Shwe, the
SPDC chairman.
</P>
<P>
During the visits, the two countries agreed to set up a Joint
Commission for Bilateral Cooperation and to mutually grant
exemption of visas to each other's citizens holding diplomatic and
official passports.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral ties have been strengthened through the recent
exchange of visits by the two top leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
