<HEADLINE> Jordanian King to Visit France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan will pay an
official visit to France from July 21 to 23 at the invitation of
President Jacques Chirac, said the French presidential office on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Queen Nour, King Hussein will hold talks with
President Chirac and Prime Minister Lionel Jospin, said the same
source.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein last visited France on June 12, 1997, while
President Chirac made a visit to Jordan in October 1996.
</P>
<P>
The planned visit by King Hussein will follow that by Syrian
President Hafez al-Assad on July 16-18.
</P>
<P>
France is seeking to play a bigger role in the mediation for
relaunching the Middle East peace process which has been blocked
since mid-1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
