<HEADLINE> Over Twenty UK Firms To Exhibit in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Twenty five British companies will
exhibit at Intertestile in Shanghai October 27-29, 1998, the
British Wool Textile Export Corporation (BWTEC) announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
BWTEC has been invited to be the Partnerland country for the
1998 edition of Intertextile by the exhibition organizers, Messe
Frankfurt, according to the announcement.
</P>
<P>
As part of the Partnerland promotion, BWTEC will create a
special trend area devoted to British yarns and fabrics which will
be a central feature at the entrance to Intertextile 1998, the
corporation said.
</P>
<P>
BWTEC will also organize a series of design seminars which will
reinforce themes on a catwalk featuring international fashion
created from British fabrics during the show.
</P>
<P>
Peter Ackroyd, BWTEC Director, said: "The Chinese market has
changed hugely since our first foray into Intertextile... the show
is clearly establishing itself as an important buying event in the
Chinese calendar."  
</P>
</TEXT>
