<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Athens Stock Exchange Index Up Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The general index at the Athens
Stock Exchange closed at 2685.65 points on Monday, up 0.70 points
from the finish on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Trade was heavy with turnover at 70.7 billion drachmas (about
2.3 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sector indices were mixed with banks rising 0.95 percent,
leasing dropping 5.18 percent, insurance increasing 1.35 percent,
investments falling 2.46 percent, industry rising 1.36 percent,
construction easing 0.60 percent, holding rising 0.42 percent, and
the parallel market easing 0.45 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Athens Stock Exchange had a very bullish week with the
general index rising 6.38 percent and average daily turnover
exceeding 100 billion drachmas (about 3.3 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Total weekly turnover was 519.5 billion drachmas (about 17.3
billion dollars), up from 387 billion drachmas (about 12.9 billion
dollars) the previous week.  
</P>
