<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosions Damages Athens Court Complex </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Two bombs exploded at the Athens
court complex Monday evening, causing damages but no injures.
</P>
<P>
The first explosion occurred at court building No. 2 at around
7 p.m. local time and the second at No. 3 at about 7:50 p.m. local
time, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said that they did not rule out the possibility that the
blasts were in connection to the shots fired at the office of
prosecutor Georgios Gerakis, who is currently investigating the
alleged police corruption.
</P>
<P>
Fearing further explosions, police are checking security
measures at the court complex.
</P>
<P>
Greece is now experiencing a wave of violent crimes as
explosions take place almost every day throughout the country.
</P>
