found under sea oil fields with rich reserves, an official said
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Albina Assis, Minister of Petroleum, told Angola Information
monthly that because of the new findings in under sea and
deep-sea rich oil fields, Angola is to turn out one million
barrels of oil by 2000 per day and 1.3 million by 2003.
</P>
