<HEADLINE> Cyprus' Missile Plan to Be Responded: Turkish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash said Monday that Turkey will retaliate if the Cypriot
government finally deploys S-300 missiles on the divided island,
according to Turkish Cypriot news agency TAK.
</P>
<P>
"Our position today stands at a point that you will get a
response to whatever you do," said Denktash in a meeting with a
Turkish Foreign Ministry delegation visiting the Turkish
Cypriots-controlled northern part of the Mediterranean island.
</P>
<P>
Denktash made the statement as Russian President Boris Yeltsin
and his Cypriot counterpart Glafcos Clerides confirmed in Moscow
that they will go ahead with the missile deal.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest agreement between Nicosia and Moscow,
the missiles will be delivered and deployed in Cyprus by the end
of November.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus signed a contract with Russia early last year to buy the
Russian-made S-300 missiles in an effort to boost its defense,
angering Turkish Cypriots and Turkey who said their security is
threatened by the missiles.
</P>
<P>
Ankara has vowed to use all possible means to prevent the
missiles from entering the small island, calling the deployment
"a direct and serious threat" to Turkish Cypriots and Turkey
itself.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into Greek Cypriot-dominated south and
Turkish Cypriot-controlled north since 1974 when Turkish troops
landed and took over the northern third of the island in the wake
of a pro-Athens coup.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz said last week that his
country would increase its military presence on the island in
response to the missiles' deployment. At present, 35,000-strong
Turkish troops are stationed on the northern side of the island.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has been provided political, economic and military
support to Turkish Cypriots and is the sole country to recognize
the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" unilaterally declared by
Turkish Cypriots in 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
