<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Small, Medium-Sized Firms in Critical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The small and medium-sized
companies (SMCs) in Romania are in critical condition, most of
them having a small turnover, said the National Union of the
Romanian Employers Monday.
</P>
<P>
An analysis on 300,000 SMCs of the existing 500,000 showed that
over one half of them have a small turnover, under 50 million
lei (about 5,700 U.S. dollars). There are even companies with zero
lei turnover.
</P>
<P>
Half of the the companies with sales figure up to 1 billion lei
(about 110,000 U.S. dollars) had recorded losses or account profit
smaller than 2 percent of their turnover, the analysis also
showed.
</P>
<P>
President of the National Union of the Romanian Employers
Stefan Chelariu said that the SMCs are blocked by causes such as
high-leveled fiscality, prohibitionary interest rates, the reduced
valorization of the financing resources dedicated to the Romanian
entrepreneurs, and high-leveled rents.
</P>
<P>
Among the strategic objectives proposed by the union are the
intrinsic privatization of the SMCs with still state majority
capital by the end of this year, the definition and delimitation
of SMCs of the rest of economic operators and their three-levels'
structuring, the entire cut or 80 percent reduction of reinvested
profit tax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
