<HEADLINE> U.S. Denies Ties With Cuban Exile Bomber </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. State Department said
Monday that it had no relations for decades with a Cuban exile who
contended his efforts to depose Cuban President Fidel Castro by
violent means were financed by a U.S. group.
</P>
<P>
Luis Posada Carriles, who once worked for the Central
Intelligence Agency (CIA), told his story in a series of
interviews with The New York Times.
</P>
<P>
