series of bombings in Cuba last year at hotels, discos and
restaurants, killing an Italian tourist in September.
</P>
<P>
Posada, 70, who was trained in demolition and guerrilla warfare
by the CIA, said the bombings were supported by the anti-Castro
Cuban-American National Foundation in Miami.
</P>
<P>
"We have not had a relationship with this person in decades,"
State Department spokesman James P. Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Posada was schooled in demolition and guerrilla warfare by the
CIA in the 1960s, according to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
