<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Drivers Subject to Point System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing drivers will be subject to
a point system beginning Wednesday, with accumulated points
determining the need for driver's education courses or other
specified penalties.
</P>
<P>
The system includes points for various offenses, including
various levels of intoxication, driving in the wrong lanes,
turning left at a pedestrian crossing, and displaying an
inappropriate license plate.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Public Security Bureau indicates that drivers can
also be cited for other 98 violations rated between one and 12
points.
</P>
<P>
Drivers exceeding 12 points in one year will be required to
attend an 18-hour intense road safety training course and pass an
examination prior to the reissuance of their license.
</P>
<P>
Licenses for those refusing to attend required classes will be
revoked, according to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
Individuals operating motor vehicles without a valid license
will be subject to penalties according to law.
</P>
<P>
Public Security officials note that the regulations are
expected to ensure road safety by curbing the notoriously poor
driving practices in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
