<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Israel to Halt Expansion of Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of the
United Nations on Monday called on Israel not to proceed with its
decision to expand the boundaries of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In a presidential statement, the Security Council called
Israel's decision to expand the boundaries of Jerusalem a "serious
and damaging development."
</P>
<P>
The statement came after the Council held a open debate on
Israel's move June 30 during which more than 40 speakers urged
Israel to halt its decision.
</P>
<P>
The Council also called on Israel not to take other steps which
would prejudice the outcome of the permanent status negotiations
between Israel and the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The Council demanded Israel abide scrupulously by its legal
obligations and responsibilities under the Forth Geneva Convention
of 1949 relating to the protection of civilians in time of war.
</P>
<P>
The Council stressed that it would keep Israeli actions under
review.
</P>
<P>
The Government of Israel approved on June 21 the decision to
expand the boundaries of Jerusalem. 
</P>
