<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Flood Control Preparations Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China is currently entering the
annual flood season and the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters today issued a circular urging all localities prepare
to protect the well-being and property of possibly affected people.
</P>
<P>
The circular noted that water levels have exceeded the flood
stage in the lower reaches of the Yangtze River. The rain zone has
moved to north and northeast China where heavy rainfall will quite
likely cause surging currents on rivers, including the Yellow
River, the country's second longest.
</P>
<P>
Two or more tropical storms or typhoons are likely to hit coastal
areas in July, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The document called on local governments to adequately prepare
for flood control by stocking both goods and materials, as well as
to reinforce water conservation projects and repair and clear
waterways to ensure the smooth flow of flood waters.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to guarantee that people in
flood-stricken areas have adequate food, drinking water, clothing,
shelters and medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
The circular stressed that the diversion of funds earmarked for
flood control for any other purpose is strictly prohibited and any
violations involving misallocations will be subject to severe
punishment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
