<HEADLINE> France Considers Applying to Host Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- After successfully playing host to
the 1998 World Cup football tournament, France is considering to
apply for the hosting of the 2008 Olympic games in Paris,
according to Agence France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
"We will study the possibility of an Olympic candidature, as we
are encouraged by the success of the World Cup," Paris mayor Jean
Tiberi told AFP during the National Day garden party at the Elysee
presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
But he said that the city will be very prudent in
decision-making over the issue, because it needs agreement from
all levels to make all elements converge.
</P>
<P>
"An Olympic candidature is not decided like that (World
Cup). One needs a certain number of agreements which engage many
people, to begin with the government and several local
communities," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tiberi said that when applying for hosting Olympics, Paris will
also take into account the calendar the Olympics and potential
rival cities.
</P>
<P>
Five cities -- Osaka, Toronto, Istanbul, Seville and Buenos
Aires have expressed interest in being the candidates for the
Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
