<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Leaders Agree to Bolster Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
Premier Zhu Rongji held a meeting and talks today, respectively,
on separate occasions with Russian Prime Minister Sergei Kiriyenko
and the leaders of both countries pledged to continue their
efforts to develop bilateral relations based on equality and
mutual trust oriented to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko, who paid a one-day working visit to China at the
invitation of his Chinese counterpart Zhu Rongji, exchanged views
with Chinese leaders on bilateral relations and major world issues
of common concern in a friendly, candid, and practical atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Kiriyenko discussed matters relating to the informal
summit between the two heads of state scheduled for early
September this year, and both were of the same view that the
coming summit will be very important. They expressed determination
to join their efforts to ensure the success of the summit.
</P>
<P>
Zhu and Kiriyenko agreed that since the initiation of the
mechanism for regular meetings between prime ministers of the two
countries in December 1996, it has played an important role in
stimulating bilateral economic and trade cooperation. Both
expressed the willingness to further increase the efficiency and
vigor of meetings, and urged the working committee and all
sub-committees to accelerate efforts to prepare for the fourth
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from the two countries also touched on the most urgent
issues in bilateral economic and trade cooperation, and the
implementation of the agreements reached during the third regular
meeting between the two prime ministers held in Moscow in February
1998.
</P>
<P>
Prime ministers of the two countries pointed out that
Sino-Russian economic and trade cooperation is based on a solid
foundation, and they urged relevant departments to adopt specific
measures to implement related agreements and documents in order to
fully tap the potentials for bilateral cooperation in various
sectors, including nuclear energy, new and high technologies,
energy, civil aviation and communications.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to explore new spheres and means of
cooperation which is needed to achieve diversity in economic and
trade relations and promote cooperation between local and border
regions in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from both countries agreed that continuous development
of cooperation between China and Russia on the basis of long-term
mutual benefit not only will be in the fundamental interests of
people of the two nations, but also be an important factor in
safeguarding world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
Zhu graciously accepted Kiriyenko's invitation to pay an
official visit to Russia next year.
</P>
<P>
The Russian prime minister left here for home earlier tonight.
</P>
</TEXT>
