<HEADLINE> EU Countries Ban Entry of Senior Belarussian Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- European Union (EU) foreign
ministers have decided to impose a non-admission on all
high-ranking officials of Belarus into EU member countries.
</P>
<P>
The decision, said a European council of ministers press
release, was made at their meeting Monday through Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the ministers condemned what they called the
"violation by Belarus of the Vienna Convention on diplomatic
relations" in its eviction of European envoys from residences in
Minsk.
</P>
<P>
The EU member states have already withdrawn their resident
ambassadors in the Belarussian capital and have requested
Belarussian ambassadors in EU capitals to return to Minsk.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Bulgaria, Cyprus, the Czech Republic, Estonia,
Hungary, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Iceland and Norway have all
declared to conform their policies with the EU position.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the 15-member EU and Belarus took a down turn
when the Belarussian authorities cut off electricity and water
supplies and telephone services to the EU ambassadors' residences.
</P>
<P>
Minsk said the move was for maintenance work at the residences.
</P>
<P>
The EU foreign ministers said early actions by Belarus to
respect fully the Vienna Convention would enable a return to
normal the bilateral relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
