<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floods Hit 10 Chinese Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Floods which have hit 10 Chinese
provinces in recent weeks have adversely affected 4.19 million ha
of arable land, destroyed crops on 2.05 million ha and prevented
the cultivation of an additional 640,000 ha, according to
government sources.
</P>
<P>
The State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters and the
Ministry of Water Resources report that concerned provinces and
autonomous regions have strengthened flood control efforts.
</P>
<P>
Some 96,000 water pumps were used to drain 3.49 million
ha. of waterlogged fields by July 13. The fields involved had the
potential to yield crops valued at 14.6 billion yuan (1.79 US
dollars), according to statistics released by the headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, Hubei and Anhui provinces in the Yangtze River Valley
have responded quickly to flooding, as have the provinces of
Guangdong and Hunan.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi Province and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
have responded somewhat slower due to the fact that they are
either poorly equipped or are besieged with overflowing lakes,
according to the headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
