<HEADLINE> Li Peng Stresses Democratic Legislation (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, China's top legislator,
recently stressed the need for democratic legislative activities
which encourage people's participation under the guidance of Deng
Xiaoping Theory on democracy and rule of law.
</P>
<P>
Li, elected in March as chairman of the National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, China's top legislative body,
made the remark during a week-long legislative fact-finding tour
of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The NPC chairman also solicited opinions and suggestions on the
draft laws concerning the organization of village committees, land
management and higher education.
</P>
<P>
Li met with farmers in two villages and promised that revisions
to the law on village committees will further guarantee the right
of farmers to participate in the direct elections of village
leaders and will in turn place elected officials under the direct
supervision of the electorate.
</P>
<P>
Li also proposed the establishment of village congress for
larger villages, with related village representatives responsible
for local and representing the best interests of local residents.
</P>
<P>
The NPC chairman also addressed the daily management of village
affairs and that all the issues relating to the best interests of
villagers, including dues, local taxes, the distribution of
land for residential housing, family planning, volunteer work and
village enterprises must be open to the public.
</P>
</TEXT>
