<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets Macao Governor (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji met
today with Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira and stressed that
greater understanding and friendly cooperation between China and
Portugal will be helpful in ensuring the smooth transition and
transfer of power in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Zhu extended a warm welcome to the Macao governor and voiced
hope that Vieira will continue to work for a better cooperation
between China and Portugal on the Macao question.
</P>
<P>
When Portuguese Prime Minister visited China earlier this year,
Zhu said, both sides held friendly and frank talks, which had a
positive influence on the development of friendly ties and
resolution of matters related to the transition and smooth return
of Macao to the Motherland.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China and Portugal should further enhance
cooperation, and noted that the solutions to problems depends on
the two side complying with trends of the times and engaging in
friendly negotiations designed to promote the development of Macao.
</P>
<P>
Zhu stressed that Macao has its own characteristics and
advantages for development, and pledged that the Chinese
government will continue its steadfast support for Macao's
economic development and improved living standards for its people.
</P>
<P>
In addition to a few cooperation programs now between Macao
and inland areas, both sides can increase exchanges and expand
cooperation in wide-ranging fields, said Zhu, adding that the
Chinese government will support the efforts of inland
entrepreneurs to invest in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier also briefed the Macao delegation on
China's reform and opening efforts, as well as the status of
economic growth.
</P>
</TEXT>
