<HEADLINE> Swazi Voter Registration Period Extended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland's voter
registration period has been extended until the end of this
month, South African Press Association reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The registration deadline was originally set for Thursday this
week.
</P>
<P>
Chief electoral officer Robert Thwala, who announced the
extension, said there had been a poor voter turnout initially,
but people were now crowding centers to register.
</P>
<P>
Progressive movements claimed that the earlier poor turnout
was an indication that people were heeding their call for a
boycott of the elections.
</P>
<P>
The movements called for the boycott, demanding that they
should be held under a multi-party system. 
