<HEADLINE> Pacific Nations Facing Challenge: N.Zealand Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The pace and direction of the
regional and global change have brought a "challenge for small
Pacific nations, such as Fiji and New Zealand," New Zealand
Minister of Commerce and Industry John Luxton said in remarks
available here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Luxton told the annual Fiji-New Zealand Joint Business
Council's Conference, which was recently held in Fiji, that
Pacific Island countries face the challenge of deciding whether to
try to move with the change or not.
</P>
<P>
He said his country's response to globalization has been to
change its direction from one of heavy protection to one which
opens up to trade and competition progressively. "This has
improved New Zealand's position," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"While New Zealand has been buffeted by the Asian situation, we
are fundamentally sound as a result of 15 years of restructuring.
We have become more flexible, responsive, innovative and market
focused," Luxton said.
</P>
<P>
He added: "We must continue to lower costs of doing business,
open up trade and make ourselves internationally competitive."
</P>
<P>
The Fiji-New Zealand Joint Business Council's Conference, which
was established 10 years ago, provides an opportunity for business
interests from Fiji and New Zealand to discuss trade, investment
and economic opportunities and to strengthen the business
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Fiji is an important market for New Zealand, taking about 100
million U.S. dollars of New Zealand's goods and services in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets Macao Governor (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vieira praised China's reform and opening policies and resolute
measures carried out amidst the ongoing financial crisis in
Asia. He stressed that the farsightedness of the "one country, two
systems" policy, and noted that Portugal and China can solved many
issues by engaging in negotiations under the guidance of the
principle.
</P>
<P>
He said Macao is capable of retaining its political and
economic systems, and expressed hope that Portugal and China will
increase cooperation and negotiations in the future.
</P>
<P>
Macao, a region bordering on the south China city of Zhuhai, has
maintained a sound cooperative relations with the European Union
(EU) and all Portuguese-speaking countries, said Vieira, adding
that such relations will enable Macao to give full play to its
role as a bridge with the economic links worldwide,
</P>
<P>
Vieira expressed hope that the Chinese side will support the
suggestions of businesspeople from Macao concerning the
construction of large-scale infrastructure, including the proposed
deep water wharf and extending the Guangzhou-Zhuhai Railway to the
region.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that Macao will strengthen cooperation with the EU
in wide-ranging areas, including science, and expressed hope that
China will make full use of Macao's advantages as a bridge to the
outside world.
</P>
<P>
Vieira pointed out that so doing will not only boost Macao's
development, but will also help to ensure a smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed confidence in the efforts of the Macao government
to handling matters related to the transition, and improving the
region's social security system. He said the Chinese government
will fully support Portuguese measures favorable to Macao's social
stability and economic growth. 
</P>
