<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 23 Killed, 5 Injured in Road Accident in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three people were killed
and five others injured in a car accident Monday night in the
northeastern province of Khorasan in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Head of the provincial traffic police Colonel Mahmoud Mohebi
told the official news agency IRNA Thursday that the accident
occurred on the road from Mashhad, the provincial capital, to
Chenaran, 75 kilometers northwest of Mashhad.
</P>
<P>
He said a car driven by a woman from Shiraz, Fars province in
southern Iran, to Mashhad collided with a tanker and the tanker
deviated from its course and had a head-on collision with an
upcoming minibus.
</P>
<P>
Mohebi said that six passengers of the car and the minibus were
instantly killed on the site and 17 others later died on their way
to hospital,
</P>
<P>
Four of the injured have been hospitalized and the driver of
the tanker was discharged from the hospital after receiving
necessary treatment.
</P>
<P>
Experts held the car driver responsible for the accident for
having diverted the vehicle to the upcoming lane. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
