The NZSE40 Index ended 38 points higher at 2,078 with a
turnover of 65.25 million dollars (34 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Energy led the rises, jumping 22 cents to 530 cents.
Telecom and Lion Nathan soared 19 cents and 18 cents to 830 cents
