<P>
He noted that while not a mediator in the Middle East issue,
China, a permanent member of the UN Security Council, will join
the international community in extending greater efforts to
promote peace in order to contribute to breaking the current
stalemate.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to China's principled stance in supporting the just
cause of Palestine and said that the Chinese government is greatly
concerned about the situation in the Middle East and the peace
process.
</P>
<P>
China firmly believes that relevant UN resolutions and the "Land
for Peace" principle are the basis for Middle East peace talks,
said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
He said that conflicts between Palestine and Israel over the
past five decades have brought tremendous disaster and suffering
to people in the region and have not only damaged security and
stability in the region, but have also hindered economic
development and prosperity of the countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said it is both fair and reasonable for the Palestinian side
to ask the Israeli government to implement the agreements between
the two sides in a down-to-earth manner.
</P>
<P>
He said that realizing peace and stability in the region at an
early date is the common aspiration of all people, including the
Israeli people. Zhu noted that the Palestinian issue
will eventually be solved due with the joint efforts of Palestine
and Israel and with assistance from the international community.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed his appreciation for the wise and practical
policies adopted by the Palestinian government.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the traditional friendship between China
and Palestine, and expressed China's admiration for the great
efforts to practice self-rule in Palestine. Zhu said China will
continue to render all possible assistance.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said that Palestine values the friendship between the
two peoples and the friendly and cooperative relations between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Palestine should draw on China's notable achievements in
political, economic and social development, according to Arafat.
</P>
<P>
On the Mideast peace process, he noted that the peace process
is at a standstill and the Palestinian people continue to face
great difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, Arafat said, the Palestinian people are determined
to remain united, meet all challenges and continue their efforts
to achieve a permanent peace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
