<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Officials Barred from Social Group Posts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Officials of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) and governments at and above the county level will
be barred from holding concurrent posts in social organizations,
according to a joint circular issued today by the Party and
government.
</P>
<P>
The new restriction on officials is part of China's ongoing
political and economic reform, according to the circular issued by
the general offices of the CPC Central Committee and the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
The new rule will promote the work of separating government
functions from business management, bring the role of mass
organizations into full play as social media, and ensure
"officials concentrate on official responsibilities," according to
the circular.
</P>
<P>
The document covers Communist Party committees officials at and
above the county level, as well as officials in people's
congresses, administrative agencies, political consultative
conference committees, courts and procuratorates.
</P>
<P>
Officials holding concurrent posts in nongovernmental groups
without appropriate authorization must resign within six months
from this month.
</P>
<P>
The circular pointed out that the People's Liberation Army will
formulate a similar rule in line with the directive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
