<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index Climbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwait Stock Exchange
continued its recovery Tuesday for the third day, with the index
picking up 29.8 points to 2,079.6 points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 85.81 million shares changed hands in over 1,928
deals as against 59.61 million shares in 1,783 deals Monday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover rose to 14.60 million Kuwaiti dinars (48.18
million U.S. dollars) from Monday's 12.42 million Kuwaiti dinars
(40.98 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Kuwait Stock Exchange index dropped to 1,996.8 points last
Saturday, the first time below the 2,000-point level this year.
</P>
<P>
But the market bounced back Sunday, edging up 38.6 points,
followed by a moderate 14.4 rise on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts remained cautious so far about the recovery,
despite the reports that the Kuwaiti government would announce
specific economic measures to shore up the market. An interventio
by the central bank was also speculated.
</P>
<P>
Such reports were believed to have boosted confidence among
investors, pushing the market up in the past days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
