<HEADLINE> Fewer Young Drug Abusers in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The number of young drug abusers
in Hong Kong dropped by 8.6 percent in the first quarter of 1998
compared with a year ago, according to the Central Registry of
Drugs Abuse (CRDA).
</P>
<P>
Overall there is a 3.3 percent drop to 6,103 in the number of
drug abusers of all ages, according to a report released by CRDA
Tuesday at a quarterly meeting of the Action Committee Against
Narcotics (ACAN).
</P>
<P>
Among the drug abusers reported in the first quarter, those
aged below 21 accounted for 1,006, down from 1,101 in the same
period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Delighted by the drop in young drug abusers, a spokesman for
ACAN said young people remain a major target of ACAN's ongoing
preventive education and publicity programs.
</P>
<P>
All the efforts are aimed at helping young people "refuse drug
offers, stay away from drugs and cope with problems in life
instead of resorting to drugs," the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
