<HEADLINE> Chirac Says Asia Financial Crisis Worries France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac said
on Tuesday that the Asia financial crisis worries France but has
so far not brought direct harm to the its economy.
</P>
<P>
In a traditional television interview on the National Day of
France, Chirac said that growth has returned to France although it
is not expected to reduce the number of chronically unemployed in
France.
</P>
<P>
"Growth has returned, there is no doubt about it. But it is
not sufficient to cut long duration unemployment," he said.
</P>
<P>
He regretted that resumption of economic growth now remains
restricted to Europe instead of around the world.
</P>
<P>
"This is a European phenomenon, it is not true for the whole
world. There is a troubling crisis in Asia, which can have
repercussion in our country, even though it has not happened up to
now, mainly thanks to the perspective of the euro which has given
confidence to the market as for what concerns Europe," he said.
</P>
