<HEADLINE> Poll: Sam Rainsy Party Most Popular in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Among the three major political
parties in Cambodia, Sam Rainsy Party appears to be the most
popular one, at least in an opinion poll published Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, by the French Institute for Statistics, Opinion Polls
and Research in Cambodia from July 8 through 11, shows that Sam
Rainsy Party enjoys support from 14.3 percent of the 3,398
respondents.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the support rate for the other two major political
parties, the Cambodian People's Party (CPP) and Funcinpec, stands
at 12.5 percent and 7.8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Other 36 parties gather only marginal support among the
respondents -- 1,595 live in Phnom Penh and 1,803 in provinces.
</P>
<P>
And while the proportion of those who expressed no opinion
remains high at 39.3 percent, it is down significantly compared to
the 58.3 percent figure in the previous survey.
</P>
<P>
The decline, however, occurs only in Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
Among the respondents who expressed no opinion, about half
claim they have not made up their mind about which party they are
going to vote for, while the other half refuse to disclose their
political preference.
</P>
<P>
Only about 2 percent say they are not interested in politics.
</P>
</TEXT>
