<HEADLINE> Tanker Drivers Threat to Strike for Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Tanker drivers in Lagos have warned
to embark on a strike if the state government could not guarantee
their safety during the lifting of fuel.
</P>
<P>
The threat followed Monday's clash between tanker drivers and
street urchins popularly known as "area boys" at a major oil
depot in the port area of Apapa.
</P>
<P>
At least two persons were feared dead and several others
injured while three tankers were torched during the fracas, the
Daily Times reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The conflict disrupted loading at the depot and would
consequently worsen the five-day-old fuel scarcity in the
nation's economic hub. 
</P>
