<HEADLINE> Bookstore-Bar Combinations Becoming Popular In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A number of distinct
bookstore-bars have recently opened in China's capital in response
to greater demand for different ways to use leisure time and
increased competition among bookstores.
</P>
<P>
Examples are the Shenghuo Dushu Xinzhi Joint Bookstore, the
Guolinfeng book center, the Beijing Concert Hall, and the Wansheng
Theatre.
</P>
<P>
Ladies' Bookstore, which is popular with many of Beijing's
women, also opened a bookstore-bar near the China Art Gallery in a
more than 100-square-meter space with unusual tables and chairs
and a good selection of drinks that are surrounded by bookshelves.
</P>
<P>
People tend to show up to enjoy looking at books while they
have a drink, and shows are also presented at the bar on weekends.
</P>
<P>
Sometimes, customers can meet authors they admire and even have
a chat with them. Wang Guozhen, a well-known poet who often pays a
visit to bookstore-bars, praises the bars for offering people a
new choice. He says they even appeal to ordinary citizens. 
</P>
