<HEADLINE> U.S. Pledges 8 Million Dollars to Geneva-based Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States has pledged a
donation of more than 8 million U.S. dollars to three Geneva-based
humanitarian organizations.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 4 million dollars will go to the United Nations
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), 3.9 million to the
International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies
(IFRC) and about 173,000 to the International Organization for
Migration (IOM).
</P>
<P>
The United States requests that the UNHCR must use at least 3.3
million dollars for repatriation and reintegration of Somali
refugees in Northwest Somalia.
</P>
<P>
It also asks the IFRC to use 2.6 million dollars for funding
refugee-related activities in Benin, Ghana, Togo, Sudan, the
Liberia Region, Guinea-Bissau and the Great Lakes region, and the
rest for the four regional support operations in Southern,
Eastern, Western, and Central Africa. 
</P>
