<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Tuesday on selling pressure due
to what dealers said concern over the injection of funds to turn
around the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister Anwar
Ibrahim announced Monday a fiscal stimulus and additional
measures to restore economic growth.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index eased 0.98
of a point or 0.23 percent to 420.33 points , the all-share Emas
Index shed 0.15 of a point to 106.15, but the Industrial Index
rose 10.53 points to 865.17 while the second board index was 0.57
of a point lower at 92.50.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 324 to 196, while 181 counters were
unchanged and 222 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover fell to 97.347 million shares worth 174.028
million ringgit (41.633 million U.S. dollars) from 128.754 million
shares valued at 263.666 million ringgit (63.077 million dollars)
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover declined to 92.916 million shares
valued at 167.582 million ringgit (40 million dollars) from
124.855 million shares worth 258.868 million ringgit (61.93
million dollars) traded Monday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover rose to 4.431 million shares worth
6.446 million ringgit (1.542 million dollars) from Monday's 3.899
million shares valued at 4.797 million ringgit (1.147 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off market deals fell to 904,216 million shares valued at 2.378
million ringgit (0.568 million dollars) from Monday's 4.354
million shares worth 11.440 million ringgit (2.736 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.261
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 7.570
million shares, construction 6.188 million shares,
trading/services 12.404 million shares, infrastructure 1.307
million shares, finance 22.476 million shares, hotels 491,000
shares, properties 11.634 million shares, plantation 4.469 million
shares, mining 309,200 shares, trusts 50,000 shares, closed/fund
58,000 shares and loans 8.698 million shares. 
</P>
