<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets With Arafat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, in a meeting with the President of the State of
Palestine Yasser Arafat today, said that the best way to resolve the
Mideast issue is negotiation based on UN resolutions and the
"Land for Peace" principle.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the Palestinian question is the key to the Mideast
issue and that China has always sympathized with and supported the
just cause of the Palestinian people, and is aware of the
complexity of the Mideast issue and the difficulty of finding a
solution.
</P>
<P>
However, China believes that as long as the Palestinian people
are united and stick to principles and flexible and pragmatic
tactics they will attain their lofty goal of regaining their lost
land and rights, and establishing an independent Palestinian
state, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He praised Arafat's contributions to the national liberation of
Palestine and said that Arafat has the support of the Palestinian
people and the respect of people all over the world with his
struggle over the past five decades and said that even ordinary
Chinese like villagers in remote areas know Arafat's name.
</P>
<P>
Li said that it is only when a statesman places the national
and the people's interests above anything else that he can win the
support of the people and a place in history.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said that the Chinese and Palestinians have a deep
friendship and leaders of the two countries have had constant
contacts, and that he is satisfied with the bilateral friendship
and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese have always stood by the Palestinian people
whenever Palestine was having difficulties and that the
Palestinians appreciate and value the Chinese people's assistance
and friendship, and said the Chinese are true friends of the
Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
Arafat said that the Mideast peace process has suffered
setbacks and that Palestine finds itself in a very difficult
situation. Peace is its strategic choice, he said, and emphasized
that the Palestinian people will continue to forge ahead until
they regain all their legitimate rights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
