<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Major Rivers Cross Danger Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's major rivers Tuesday
crossed the danger level at many places due to heavy rain in the
past few days, according to sources of the country's Flood
Information Center (FIC).
</P>
<P>
The Bhrahmaputra river crossed the danger level at four places,
and it continues to flow 21 and 34 centimeters above the danger
level at two places.
</P>
<P>
The Ganges registered further sharp rise by 34, 28, 22, 18 and
4 centimeters above the red mark at five places.
</P>
<P>
All other major rivers such as Jamuna, Teesta, Padma, Karatoa,
Punarbhaba, Gorai, Kumar, Meghna and Muhur register by 6
centimeters to 4.16 meters above the danger level.
</P>
<P>
Besides, all rivers in the southeastern hill basin also
registered further rise at all points, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Over two million people have been affected and one million
acres of crops damaged by floods in this South Asian country.
</P>
<P>
All the people in the affected areas are now combating the
flood. 
</P>
</TEXT>
