<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- France on Tuesday held its annual
national day military parade on the Champs-Elysee boulevard in
Paris, in the wake of a national celebration for the winning of
the World Cup football championship by France on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
President Jacques Chirac, Prime Minister Lionel Jospin and some
150,000 people attended the parade under sun-shine and breeze.
</P>
<P>
