<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Open Stock Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is to open stock exchanges
in both Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City this october, Vietnam's English
daily "Vietnam News" reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Prime Minister Phan Van Khai signed the decision
approving the securities trading centers - or stock exchanges -
last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The decision says the centers will have responsibility for the
following major tasks:
</P>
<P>
-- organizing, managing and overseeing the buying and selling
of securities.
</P>
<P>
-- managing and implementing the securities trading system.
</P>
<P>
-- providing the services necessary to the buying and selling
of securities and a depository service.
</P>
<P>
-- registering securities.
</P>
<P>
-- settling and clearing securities transactions.
</P>
<P>
-- making information about securities transactions public.
</P>
<P>
-- monitoring and supervising securities transactions.
</P>
<P>
-- collecting fees for: the listing of securities membership
services and other costs according to law.
</P>
<P>
-- providing reports, statistics and auditing in accordance
with state regulations.
</P>
<P>
The securities trading centers will be the responsibility of
Vietnam's State Securities Committee which was established in late
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
