<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese Trade Fair Results Better Than Expected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Qingdao Foreign Economic
and Trade Fair, which concluded on Sunday, had 950 million
U.S. dollars worth of contracts, a better than expected result.
</P>
<P>
The figure was slightly lower than the previous
session, but the number of infrastructure, light industry, and
technology projects increased.
</P>
<P>
Agreements on 751 foreign-funded projects were signed, worth
1.9 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports accounted for 810 million U.S. dollars worth of trade
deals, with exports to Asian countries down 18 percent and exports
to Europea and the U.S. showing a notable increase.
</P>
<P>
Products of large domestic manufacturers like Haier, Qingqi
Motors, and Langchao were well received at the fair. The Haier
Group signed a 11.2 million U.S. dollar contract with a Turkish
company.
</P>
<P>
Details of the '98 Qingdao Fair are available on the Internet
and there is a special 'Qingdao Trade Fair on the Net' column on
Yahoo. Some 100,000 people from more than 20 countries and regions
have visited these websites and 100 enterprises have found trade
partners in this way.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has one of the fastest-growing economies in eastern
China and excels in foreign trade in grains, oil, foodstuff,
machinery, minerals, home appliances, textiles, handicrafts,
building materials, and the chemical industry.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, its foreign trade volume rose to 19.7 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
