<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Sets Up Foundation to Promote People to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) established here Tuesday a foundation to promote
and strengthen people to people contact.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to have an institution that will promote people to
people contact. What we would not like to see is for ASEAN to
develop as an inter-governmental organization only," Indonesian
Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said after the establishment ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"Through the foundation, we hope to energize a lot of projects.
Of the ASEAN Foundation, much can be expected and a great deal
will be demanded," he said, adding that the foundation will
promote human resources development, education, skills training,
health care and culture.
</P>
<P>
The organization will offer fellowships and establish an
exchange program for ASEAN youths, scientists and professionals,
the minister said.
</P>
<P>
It will also take initiatives to address urgent regional
concerns, including efforts to alleviate poverty, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile ASEAN Secretary General Rodolfo C. Severino said the
foundation could promote ASEAN awareness as well as social
cohesiveness.
</P>
<P>
With regard to the current economic crisis, Severino said that
a crucial task of the foundation is to help restore international
confidence in ASEAN economies.
</P>
<P>
The idea of setting up the foundation was first brought up
during the 1st ASEAN Informal Summit Meeting held in Jakarta in
December 1996.
</P>
<P>
At the second ASEAN Informal Summit Meeting in Kuala Lumpur,
Malaysia, in 1997, a memorandum of understanding on the
establishment of the foundation was signed by the ASEAN foreign
ministers.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar, Laos, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
