<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Troika Delegation to Resume Dialog With Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced Tuesday that the
European Union (EU) is to resume its "critical dialog" with Iran
Saturday to pave the way for improving the strained EU-Iran
relations.
</P>
<P>
Ali Ahani, director general for Western European affairs at
the Iranian Foreign Ministry, said that the EU Troika delegation
comprising Austrian, British and German officials would arrive
here Friday and start the first round of talks Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ahani was quoted by the official news agency IRNA as saying
that the main topics of the talks would be the EU-Iran cultural
cooperation as well as the relation between the EU and the
Organization of the Islamic Conference.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the three-day visit, the EU Troika
delegation would also discuss with Iranian officials the latest
developments in Afghanistan, Iraq, Central Asia and the Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
The EU visit was originally scheduled in June, but delayed due
to the differences over the delegation's level and the agenda.
</P>
<P>
Ahani expressed the hope that the talks would result in
positive and constructive developments in Iran-EU relations.
</P>
<P>
Iranian officials said earlier that Iran expected the EU to
send a high-level delegation to start a "constructive dialog" to
replace the "critical dialog," which was launched by the EU in
December 1992 in a bid to milden Iran's policies on the Middle
East peace process, terrorism and weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
The EU suspended the "critical dialog" in April last year after
a Berlin court ruling accused top Iranian officials of sponsoring
terrorist activities against Iranian dissidents in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Ending the diplomatic row over the Berlin court issue, the EU
decided in last March to resume ministerial contacts and the
"critical dialog" with Iran.
</P>
<P>
To pave the way for improving the EU-Iran relations, Italian
Prime Minister Romano Prodi paid an official visit to Iran early
this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
