<HEADLINE> Philippine President Orders Sugar Importation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
has authorized the immediate importation of sugar to avert any
possible shortage of the commodity, a news release from the
Presidential Palace said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Estrada also directed the chairman of the Minimum Access Volume
Management Committee to finalize by July 16 the guidelines
enabling the country to import sugar under the 50 percent in-quota
tariff before July 31.
</P>
<P>
