<HEADLINE> Chinese, Russian Premiers Start Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and his
Russian counterpart Sergei Kiriyenko started talks shortly after
the latter's arrival here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The talks will focus on the mechanism of meetings between the
premiers of the two countries and the continued promotion of
bilateral economic and trade cooperation, sources said.
</P>
<P>
At the press time, the talks are still going on.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Premier Zhu is expected to host a dinner in
honor of Prime Minister Kiriyenko, who is here as Zhu's guest for
a five-hour working visit.
</P>
<P>
Later today, Chinese President Jiang Zemin will also meet with
Kiriyenko, who is scheduled to leave here for home late in the
evening.
</P>
<P>
This is Prime Minister Kiriyenko's first visit to China since
he assumed office in April this year.  
