<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Merrill Lynch Plans to Expand China Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Merrill Lynch of the United States
will significantly expand its business in China, according to
David Komansky, the company chairman.
</P>
<P>
"Merrill Lynch will continue to be a partner with China in
countless ways, as a link to the capital markets worldwide, as an
advisor to government and private enterprises, and even one day to
Chinese families and individuals who will face the same crucial
financial decisions as their counterparts all over the globe,"
Komansky said at a ceremony here marking his receiving of the
Marco Polo Prize, which is granted by the China Project of the
Volunteers of America.
</P>
<P>
Komansky also urged China to open its financial sector wider to
pave the way for greater involvement of overseas investment banks
in China's capital market.
</P>
<P>
"Like every great nation, China has the daunting economic
challenge of providing financial security for a growing elderly
population. And Merrill Lynch can be an enormous assistant giving
people the tools to save and invest to become more self-sufficient
and less dependent on their government for their economic
well-being," the chairman said.
</P>
<P>
"This, of course, requires government action to encourage
companies like Merrill Lynch to become more involved in the
domestic service system, and it also requires the further
development of the regulatory structure to protect the individual
investors as well as the provider of the financial services," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Komansky also said that he is fully confident about China's
ability to overcome the effects of the Asian financial crisis and
to push forward domestic financial reforms.
</P>
<P>
The first United States securities firm to open representative
offices in China, Merrill Lynch has so far underwritten Chinese
shares and bonds valued at eight billion U.S. dollars, the largest
business volume in China among all overseas investment banks.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Merrill Lynch manages 13 trillion US dollars in
customer assets.
</P>
<P>
The Marco Polo Prize is awarded to individuals and collectives
that have rendered active support to the China Project of the
Volunteers of America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
