<HEADLINE> Shanghai Eager to Develop Consultancy Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- This economic and financial
center of China will increase its effort to develop the
consultancy industry, according to Vice Mayor Zuo Huanchen.
</P>
<P>
"We'll step up our effort to develop the consultancy industry
to meet the challenge of a knowledge-based economy," Zuo said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Shanghai had more than 7,380
consultancy agencies by the end of last year employing nearly
100,000 professionals. These agencies had a combined income of
3.37 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is now undergoing a period of industrial restructuring
and the consultancy industry has great market potential, Zuo said.
</P>
<P>
He also said that active efforts should be made to launch
consultancy services on electronic networks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
