<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sales of Commonwealth Games Tickets Slow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Tickets are only selling
slowly for the Commonwealth Games in Malaysia in September.
</P>
<P>
"Until now, tickets to the Commonwealth Games does not enjoy
brisk sales," Loke Yuen Yow, deputy minister of the youth and
sports ministry was quoted as saying by the Malay daily Utusan
Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Loke said that up to July 4, only 42,811 tickets valued at four
million ringgit (956,938 U.S. dollars) were sold in Malaysia --
the host country while 29,719 tickets worth three million ringgit
were abroad.
</P>
<P>
Minister Loke said a number of promotional measures have been
launched to stimulate sales.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is the first Asian country to Stage the Commonwealth
Games in their 68-year history. The games officials said the
operational budget for the games was 310 million ringgit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
