<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Estate Market Recovering In Southern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The real estate business has been
picking up in the port city of Beihai on the Beibu Gulf in the
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of this year, there was 389 million
yuan in real estate trading, a 58 percent increase from the same
period last year, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The price of apartments in Beihai has gone from 800 to 1,000
yuan per square meter to 1,200 to 1,500 yuan, and although the
price of flats in the Yinwan Gardens, a Construction Ministry
comfortable-housing model, has doubled, there is no lack of buyers
and all the flats have been sold.
</P>
<P>
The Beihai City Real Estate Trading Center reports 1,405 deals
in the January to June period, up 22.8 percent from last year,
with housing sales up 52 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attribute the business increase to the Central
Government's decision to treat housing as a new economic growth
area and to the improved urban infrastructure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic Growth In Shanghai's Pudong In First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The economy in Shanghai's Pudong
New Area had 15.1-percent growth in the first half of this year,
5.7 percent more than for the city overall.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's GDP had a 15.1-percent increase at 29.3
billion yuan, and industrial output value of 64.5 billion yuan by
the end of June, up 15.8 percent for the same six-month period of
last year. Exports grew 18 percent to 2.4 billion U.S. dollars worth.
</P>
<P>
A local trade official gives three reasons for the rapid
economic growth:
</P>
<P>
-- Tertiary trade, with finance in the lead, maintaining rapid
growth.
</P>
<P>
-- Some 2,000 foreign-funded enterprises beginning operation.
</P>
<P>
-- Export of foreign-funded industrial firms rose 53
percent. The growth in exports to Europe and the United states was
greater than the rate of decline in exports to Southeast Asia.
</P>
</TEXT>
