<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoid Fever Kills 8 in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Department of Health Tuesday
confirmed the typhoid fever outbreak in the central Philippine
town of Samar which killed eight people recently.
</P>
<P>
Lilia Arteche, Eastern Visayas health regional director, said
the outbreak of typhoid fever was reportedly caused by
contamination of a brook transversing three hinterland villages.
</P>
<P>
The contamination of the said stream, the only source of water
in the villages, could be attributed to the long summer months due
to the El Nino phenomenon aside from the possibility that some
residents may have defecated in it, Arteche said.
</P>
<P>
She said that the outbreak has been placed under control with
cases starting to decrease as continuous monitoring of illnesses
is being conducted by the regional health office.
</P>
<P>
Medicines were also sent to the villages, Arteche said.
</P>
<P>
Typhoid fever is caused by ingestion of food and water
contaminated with human waste.
</P>
<P>
Among the signs and symptoms are sustained high fever,
headache, weakness, loss of appetite, diarrhea or constipation and
abdominal discomfort. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top High-tech Exporters Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China has recently announced its
top 10 high-tech exporters.
</P>
<P>
They are Guangdong Province, Beijing and Shanghai
municipalities, Jiangsu Province, Tianjin Municipality, and Liaoning,
Fujian, Shandong, Zhejiang and Heilongjiang provinces.
</P>
<P>
The export value of high-tech products from these 10 areas made up
95 percent of the national total with each surpassing 100 million
U.S. dollars in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The export value of south China's Guangdong Province totaled
4.3 billion yuan, ranking first in the nation.
</P>
<P>
Processed goods using imported materials have been the
principal high-tech import and export items. 
</P>
</TEXT>
