<HEADLINE> Large Natural Gas Field Discovered In Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A large amount of proven natural
gas reserves has been reported in Sichuan Province in southwestern
China.
</P>
<P>
The Kaijiang Natural Gas Field, located in the eastern part of
the Sichuan Basin, is believed to have 90 billion cubic meters
of gas.
</P>
<P>
After years of exploration, the area has 11 wells with a daily
output of 500 cubic meters of natural gas in a
4,500-square-kilometer area, and geologists are looking for more
gas fields in the area, which is believed to have huge potential
for development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
