<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert Raises New View of Sustainable Financial Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A new view of sustainable
financial development raised by Professor Bai Qinxian has evoked
wide discussion in China's financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Bai Qinxian, director of the International Financial Institute
attached to Liaoning University, published his financial views in
early June and they were met with an immediate response in the
print media and at seminars.
</P>
<P>
According to Bai, sustainable financial development refers to
the establishment and perfection of the financial system, the
development of its mechanisms and the improvement of financial
efficiency while following the inherent law of financial
development, so that these resources can be distributed in an
efficient way while the economy maintains healthy development.
</P>
<P>
Bai pointed out that the world's economy and finance are
becoming increasingly global, with finance playing a growing role
in this new worldwide economy.
</P>
<P>
"Finance has extreme strategic importance in the stability of
China's and the world's economic and social development. "Finance
is one of a country's most precious strategic resources, which
should be appropriately tapped for sustainable long-term
development," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that sustainable economic development can not do
without sustainable financial development, and suggested that the
government include sustainable financial development in China's
"21st Century Agenda."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expert Raises New View of Sustainable Financial Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Many financial experts called Bai's viewpoint a breakthrough
beyond the traditional theoretical system, and said they believe
it will enable people to gain a new understanding of the core
function of modern finance in resource distribution and social and
economic operations. They may also reconsider the importance of
financial safety and financial sovereignty to a nation's safety
and sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Experts also pointed out that although the idea of sustainable
financial development has yet to be fully implemented, it can help
solve the problems of financial crises, development and
supervision.
</P>
<P>
Since the Southeast Asian financial crisis erupted in mid-1997,
China's scholars have stepped up their examinations of finance in
an effort to find a financial operating model suited to China's
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government also stepped up its financial reform
this year, giving full play to financial levers on macroeconomic
control while trying to prevent financial risks.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics released by the People's Bank of China,
the central bank, show that the financial sector operated smoothly
in the first half of this year, with the RMB yuan remaining
stable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
