<HEADLINE> Houston Set WNBA Winning Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Houston Comets set a WNBA
record with their ninth straight win Monday as they beat the
Washington Mystics 81-67.
</P>
<P>
Cynthia Cooper had 23 points and a season-high eight assists
and her teammate Sheryl Swoopes added 21 points and Janeth Arcain
matched a season high with 14 off the bench for the Comets. The
winning team, with a 14-1 record, bettered the eight-game streak
compiled last season by Cleveland. Houston also broke a league
record with their eighth straight home win, seven of which have
come by double digits.
</P>
<P>
Alessandra Santos de Oliveira had her second straight-double
with 14 points and 12 rebounds, and Nikki McCray also scored 14
points for the Mystics (2-12), who led the defending champions
early in the second half before losing for the ninth time in 10
games.
</P>
<P>
