Starzz 74-67, while the Phoenix Mercury defeated the Los Angeles
Sparks 72-62.
</P>
<P>
Sandy Brondello scored 23 points and Korie Hlede added 19 to
help the Shcok snap a four-game losing streak. Wendy Palmer
contributed 19 points for the Starzz (4-11), who have lost three
straight and four of their last five games.
</P>
<P>
Phoenix scored their third straight win today. Jennifer Gillom,
the WNBA's third-leading scorer, collected 27 points and nine
rebounds for Mercury. Lisa Leslie finished with 13 points and 13
boards for Los Angeles, who opened the season with a win at Utah
but has dropped five in a row on the road since. 
</P>
