<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Republic of Montenegro in
Yugoslavia Monday staged rallies to mark the 57th anniversary of
the armed uprising against fascist invaders.
</P>
<P>
Montenegro President Milo Djukanovic, military leaders such as
Ladoslav Martinovic and Milan Zec and World War II veterans joined
the rally held at Virpazar meeting center and laid wreaths at
the martyrs' tomb.
</P>
