<HEADLINE> China Standard Service Net Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China Standard Service Net(CSSN)
is now connected with the worldwide Internet.
</P>
<P>
The website--http://www.cssn.net.cn-- provides information on
China's recommended national compulsory standards, relevant rules
and regulations, industry standards and product approval.
</P>
<P>
The new website is part of the World Standard Service Net of
the International Standardization Organization (ISO) designed to
enhance the exchange of standardization among countries, tear down
technological barriers and promote international trade in a
coordinated manner, sources said.
</P>
<P>
China is currently a member of the ISO.  
