<HEADLINE> 10 People Killed in Road Accidents in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed and
about 65 injured in separate road accidents in Bangladesh on
Monday, media reports here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Six people were killed on the spot and 28 others injured, four
of them seriously, when a loaded truck collided with a bus from
the opposite direction near Madhabpur in the country's western
district of Pabna. Another person died in hospital later.
</P>
<P>
The bus fell into a roadside ditch while the truck fled, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
In Feni, 136 kilometers southeast of here, a head-on collision
between a bus and a tempo (three-wheeled motor vehicle) on the
Dhaka-Chittagong highway left two persons dead and two others
injured.
</P>
<P>
And in Narsingdi, northeastern Bangladesh, a minibus fell into
a roadside ditch killing one and injuring 25 others.
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday, three cars of the Chittagong-bound inter-city
train "Turna-Nishitha" were derailed at the Mirsarai crossing, in
the southeastern Chittagong district, on the Chittagong-Dhaka
route slightly, injuring 10 passengers.
</P>
<P>
The three cars in the middle of the train went out of the track
when the train was leaving the Mirsarai Station, disrupting normal
train service on the route for 10 hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
