<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Builds Asia's Largest Hot Slime Rehabilitation Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A hot slime rehabilitation
center for the treatment of many kinds of chronical diseases has
been built in Anshan City in northeast China's Liaoning Province,
the largest of its kind in Asia.
</P>
<P>
With 6 million yuan (720,000 U.S. dollars) of investment, the
constant-temperature slime treatment center covers 2,600 square
meters, and doctors say the therapy is especially effective for
rheumatism and other chronic diseases.
</P>
<P>
The hot slime is a kind of weathered granite that is found
together with hot springs.
</P>
<P>
The fine grey-brown mud has a temperature of 65 degrees
Centigrade and contains more than 20 chemical elements including
iron and sodium.
</P>
<P>
Doctors here said the hot lime therapy can relieve pain,
improve blood circulation and help restore the normal functions of
muscle and joints. 
</P>
</TEXT>
