<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pursuit of Modern Family Leads to Reduction in Zhejiang Population </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The pursuit of modern family life
has led to a large population reduction in east China's Zhejiang
province, according to today's "People's Daily."
</P>
<P>
The country's leading newspaper said that the "new family"
planning program, which combines birth control with building
prosperous, happy and healthy families, has been widely accepted
by local villagers.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, 70 percent of the local families have participated
in the program, among which 152,705 were selected as models and
1,215 were lifted out of poverty.
</P>
<P>
Data from the provincial government show that at the end of
last year Zhejiang's population was 44.34 million, 140,000 less
than anticipated.
</P>
<P>
The birth rate dropped to 11.41 per thousand from 14.76 per
thousand in 1992, and the population growth rate stood at 4.93 per
thousand last year.
</P>
<P>
With the largest population in the world, China has long worked
hard to control population growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
