<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0265 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Fish Market Opens in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A fish market, the largest on the
Jiaodong Peninsular, recently opened on Sanshan Island in east
China's Shandong Province, "People's Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The market, built at a cost of 16 million yuan, has a
20,000-square-meter market-hall accommodating 5,000 booths.
</P>
<P>
To date, over 60 seafood companies from such coastal provinces
as Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Fujian and Guangdong have begun doing
business in the market. Their products are shipped to the United
States, Japan, the Republic of Korea and Hong Kong apart from
being sent to large Chinese mainland cities including Beijing,
Tianjin and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The market expects to sell 30,000 tons of seafood annually with
a trade value of 300 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The island now has 16,000 ha of water area for breeding
scallops, mussels and oysters. Over 600 fishing vessels work in
the area with an annual catch of 100,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
