<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Exxon Chemical Eastern Inc and
Jinzhou Petrochemical Co have signed a contract for a joint
venture that will use Jinzhou's old lubricant-additive factory.
</P>
<P>
They will be equal partners in the joint venture, said today's
China Daily, adding that the renovation of the old plant are
expected to begin in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Exxon will lend its latest technology to the joint venture. The
lubricant additives will bear Exxon's Paramins brand name and be
sold mostly in china's growing domestic market.
</P>
