<HEADLINE> Superbike Race Abandoned after Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The opening race was abandoned
after a crash took place on midway in the eighth round of the
world superbike championship in Laguna Seca, California on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Third-placed Doug Chandler of the United States lost his
right-hand handlebar on the 13th lap, veered off the circuit and
crashed.
</P>
<P>
His machine bounced into second-placed rider Japanese Akira
Yanagawa while Italian Pierfrancesco Chili and Briton Neil Hodgson
clashed in the dust thrown up by Chandler's Kawasaki.
</P>
<P>
Chandler sustained a minor leg injury and Yanagawa received
minor facial injuries.
</P>
<P>
The race was abandoned with Australian Troy Corner on a
Ducati leading by six seconds. Half points were awarded to the
riders. 
