<HEADLINE> Big Strides Scored for Express Mail Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China Express Mail Service
Company (EMS), a heavyweight of the country's express mail
business, has delivered about 300 million pieces of mail
generating business income of about 11 billion yuan (1.325 billion
U.S. dollars) since it began operations 18 years ago, the company
announced today.
</P>
<P>
The company's service is now available in about 2,000 Chinese
cities and linked to over 200 countries and regions around the
world.
</P>
<P>
Despite fierce market competition, EMS still accounts for over
70 percent of the domestic market and 50 percent of the
international business volume, according to Yuan Guoli, EMS's
general manager.
</P>
<P>
The utilization of modern technology has put a halt to manual
registration and enabled computerized inquiry between major
Chinese and foreign cities. Next-day delivery between ten major
inland cities and Hongkong is also available. 
</P>
