<HEADLINE> Six Thai Ministries to Undergo Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government Monday
endorsed a re-organization plan for six ministries in hope of
saving some 8 billion baht (195 million U.S. dollars), the Bangkok
Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring is part of the government's program to trim
public sector fat, Thipawadee Meksawan, secretary-general of the
Civil Service Commission, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
it covers the Agriculture Ministry, the Transport and
Communications Ministry, the Labor and Social Welfare Ministry,
the Science Ministry, the Public Health Ministry and the Industry
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Under the re-organization plan, overlapping activities will be
delegated to a single agency while activities which are related to
local administration will be transferred to local organizations.
Non-value-added work will be sub-contracted to private firms.
</P>
<P>
Non-core activities like reforestation are terminated while
activities which yield profits will be handled by a special
agency, Thipawadee said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
