<HEADLINE> Uruguay Wine Exports Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 13, (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan wine exports rose by
69 percent in the first half of 1998, compared to the same period
last year, according to a national research institute.
</P>
<P>
A report by the National Viticulture Institute showed Uruguay
had sold 487,745 liters of wine on the international market by
June 30, 197,924 more than last year.
</P>
<P>
The external sales of red wine accounted for 71 percent of the
total, followed by white and rose wine.
</P>
<P>
Britain was the main buyer, taking 167,476 liters in the first
six months, followed by Norway, Denmark, Brazil, France, Germany,
Sweden, and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Exports of Uruguayan wines totaled 1,065,740 liters in 1997,
representing an increase of 89 percent over 1996. 
</P>
