Standing Committee, met with Carl Hahn, former chairman of the
board of directors of Volkswagen AG of Germany in Changchun, the
capital of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
 China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- Statistics released Monday by the People's Bank of China
indicated that the country's financial sector has been operating
smoothly during the first half of this year, with the bank loans
and deposits increasing steadily and the Renminbi yuan remaining
stable.
</P>
<P>
-- China resents to the recent anti-China resolutions adopted
by the U.S. Senate and is in firm opposition to it, said Foreign
Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Senate passed a resolution on July 10 which requires
the Clinton administration to maintain arms sales to Taiwan.
</P>
