<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0284 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Enhance Earthquake-proofing for Highrises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- This year China will begin to step
up its administration of earthquake-proofing designs in a bid to
strengthen the capacity of buildings over 120 meters high to
withstand earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
Vice minister of construction Ye Rutang said here today that
with fast economic development and urban construction, highrise
buildings are mushrooming nationwide, with more than 300 already
built.
</P>
<P>
But a survey of building designs in a dozen cities shows that
many latent problems exist in these structures and their ability
to withstand seismic activity must be improved.
</P>
<P>
To improve the reliability and safety of the design of these
buildings, the Ministry of Construction has issued Provisional
Administrative Rules Over Anti-seismic Design for Highrises, and
set forth strict demands that designing institutes must follow in
making architectural and earthquake-proofing plans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
