<DOCNO> XIE19980714.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Nino Hits Chile Fish Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The export of aquatic products
from Chile totalled 765 million U.S. dollars in the first five
months of this year, 11.7 percent less than in the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Official figures released here on Monday suggest the drop was
the result of the El Nino phenomena, which warmed the sea near
Chile and drove fish away from the region.
</P>
<P>
Japan, which took 40.7 percent of all Chilean fish exports, was
still the largest buyer, while the United States and China
remained second and the third.
</P>
<P>
The report predicted that the fish output would rise back
slowly as El Nino vanished, but the total output this year could
not reach the level of last year.
</P>
<P>
Fish is the second largest pillar industry for exports by Chile.
</P>
<P>
Last year, fish exports earned 187.2 million dollars, making
this South American country the fifth largest fish producer in the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
