<HEADLINE> Guilin Hosts Three Million Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Guilin, a scenic city in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, hosted close to 3.3
million tourists in the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure included 147,000 overseas tourists, down 19.2
percent on the previous year's period, with the number of domestic
tourists growing by 13 percent to 3.15 million, according to the
city's tourism management department.
</P>
<P>
Figures showed that tourism generated 1.36 billion
yuan, up 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
The decline in foreign tourists was attributed to the
adverse effects of the financial crisis in Southeast Asia, which
has long been a primary source of tourism in the city.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the rapid increase in domestic
tourists to the city's intensified efforts to stage tourism
promotions and activities, as well as to the improved order of the
tourism market which promoted confidence and interest in the
beautiful city.
</P>
<P>
Guilin plans to open an Internet website in August to promote
tourism in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The city will also join hands with Xi'an, Beijing, Shanghai,
and Hong Kong to promote the "Presidential Travel" program in the
United States in order to attract more foreign tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
