<HEADLINE> Cuba, Guatemala Formally Resume Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Guatemala and Cuba formally resumed
diplomatic relations Monday for the first time in 36 years.
</P>
<P>
The Guatemalan ambassador presented his credentials to the
Cuban government, saying it was the first step in extending
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and Guatemala suspended relations after Manuel Ydigoras,
president of Guatemala from 1958 to 1963, provided a site in the
south of Guatemala City for training mercenaries who later tried
to invade Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The two countries agreed to reestablish diplomatic relations
after Pope John Paul II visited Cuba in January this year. 
</P>
