quick action on economic reforms.
</P>
<P>
"It is very important to the United States that a new
government, whatever its composition, move quickly to implement
concrete fiscal and banking measures to achieve strong domestic
demand-led growth in Japan and to restore confidence in Japan's
financial system," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We think they will see it in their own self-interest to pursue
economic reform quickly," he added.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto announced his resignation and canceled a planned on
July 22 visit to the United States after his party, the Liberal
Democratic Party, suffered heavy losses in the Upper House
election Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to call President Bill Clinton later Monday,
McCurry said. He also reiterated that Washington was consulting
with Japanese officials on a visit to the United States by
Hashimoto's successor. 
