over marches after three Catholic boys were killed in a fire-bomb
attack in the British-rule Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regular briefing, State Department spokesman
James Rubin said the death of the three boys was "an abomination."
</P>
<P>
"No commemorative march is worth the murder of children," he
said. "We regard the death of the three boys in a sectarian arson
attack as an abomination that is unjustifiable under any
circumstances."
</P>
