<HEADLINE> UNDP Helps Kenya Improve Women's Status </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) in Kenya has launched two projects
valued at 1.37 million U.S. dollars to strengthen the legal and
political status of women, UNDP said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The initiative will increase women's participation in
government and in conflict resolution processes, the U.N. segment
said in its weekly publication UNDP FLASH.
</P>
<P>
The projects will help prepare and disseminate public awareness
materials on women's rights, and conduct training programs.
</P>
<P>
Key institutions including the Attorney General's Office, the
National Assembly and the Judiciary and Electoral Commission will
receive support under the scheme. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
